gomodel:SYNGO_1413  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors investigate the role of importing alpha 1 using mouse hippocampal cultures that were silenced by using TTX or APV/CNQX. In both cases, nuclear levels of importin alpha 1 were significatively decreased, suggesting the translocation of the protein from the postsynapse to the nucleus in an NMDA receptor activation-dependent manner. They further proved the necessity of NMDA receptor activation by performing a similar experiment in the presence of TTX and simultaneous stimulation with exogenous glutamate, which trigger a similar effect in nuclear levels of importin alpha 1. Moreover, induction of chemical LTP in organotypic slices triggered an enhancement in nuclear levels of importin alpha 1 in the CA1 region of the hippocampus, which suggest that the nuclear import pathway is activated by LTP processes.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n- Whole sera containing rabbit polyclonal antibodies against mouse importin 1 (mSrp1) and importin 2 (mPendulin) were kind gifts from Marion Waterman, UC Irvine, CA.\n- Primary cultured hippocampal neurons were prepared from P0-P1 Black 6 mouse or Sprague-Dawley rat pups.\n\nExperiments were performed in mouse cultures or organotypic slices." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_1413" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
